{"metadata":{"kernelspec":{"language":"python","display_name":"Python 3","name":"python3"},"language_info":{"name":"python","version":"3.12.13","mimetype":"text/x-python","codemirror_mode":{"name":"ipython","version":3},"pygments_lexer":"ipython3","nbconvert_exporter":"python","file_extension":".py"},"kaggle":{"accelerator":"none","dataSources":[],"dockerImageVersionId":28755,"isInternetEnabled":false,"language":"python","sourceType":"notebook","isGpuEnabled":false}},"nbformat_minor":4,"nbformat":4,"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"# Visualizing Feature Engineering as a Transformation of Feature Space\n\nIn this notebook, I wanted to explore feature engineering from a slightly different perspective.\n\nFeature engineering is often discussed in terms of CV improvement, LB score, or model-specific tricks. Of course, that is very important. But at a more fundamental level, I think feature engineering can also be viewed as a way of transforming the data space into a representation that is easier for a model to understand.\n\nFor example, tree-based models often benefit from features that make useful splits more axis-aligned. Neural networks may benefit from smoother, more continuous representations. Linear models and stackers work best when the classes become closer to linearly separable. Groupby features, target encoding, frequency encoding, prior features, and OOF stacking can also be interpreted as adding new coordinates to the space — coordinates that are not directly available in each individual row.\n\nSo the question I wanted to investigate here is:\n\n> Can we visualize how feature engineering changes the geometry of the data?\n\nThis notebook is not intended to directly improve the leaderboard score. Instead, it is an exploratory notebook for understanding how different feature spaces look after dimensionality reduction. I compare several spaces:\n\n* the original raw feature space\n* a light RealMLP-style feature-engineered space\n* an expanded XGBoost-style feature-engineered space\n* an OOF stacking logit space built from multiple model predictions\n\nFor each space, I apply PCA and t-SNE to project the high-dimensional features into 2D, then color the samples by class. This allows us to observe how much the classes become separated, how the manifold changes, and how different types of feature engineering reshape the data.\n\nOf course, a 2D visualization is only a compressed view of the original high-dimensional space. It should not be interpreted as a complete explanation of model performance. Still, I think it can be a useful tool for building intuition about what feature engineering is doing.\n\n## Credits\n\nThis notebook is based heavily on the excellent public work shared by other Kaggle competitors.\n\nHuge thanks to **@cdeotte** for another set of great notebooks for this competition, especially:\n\n* **GPU Logistic Regression Stacker**\n  https://www.kaggle.com/code/cdeotte/gpu-logistic-regression-stacker\n* **RealMLP v1 for S6E6**\n  https://www.kaggle.com/code/cdeotte/realmlp-v1-for-s6e6\n* **XGB v1 for S6E6**\n  https://www.kaggle.com/code/cdeotte/xgb-v1-for-s6e6\n\nI also learned a lot from the excellent XGBoost notebook by **@donmarch14**:\n\n* **S6E6 XGBoost**\n  https://www.kaggle.com/code/donmarch14/s6e6-xgboost\n\nThe modeling ideas, feature engineering choices, and stacking setup in this notebook are inspired by these notebooks. My contribution here is mainly to reorganize them from the viewpoint of feature-space visualization and to examine how the data geometry changes across different representations.\n\nI also used Codex as a coding assistant to help implement this experiment and organize the notebook, including parts of this introduction. The main motivation was to better understand feature engineering as a transformation of feature space, and Codex helped me turn that idea into a reproducible notebook.\n\nAny mistakes or misinterpretations are, of course, my own.","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ============================================================\n# S6E6 Feature Space Visualization\n# CPU 4-core version\n#\n# Visualizes:\n#   1. raw feature space\n#   2. RealMLP-style light FE space\n#   3. XGB-style expanded FE space\n#   4. OOF stacking logit meta-feature space\n#\n# Output:\n#   /kaggle/working/feature_space_vis/*.png\n#   /kaggle/working/feature_space_vis/*_pca2.csv\n#   /kaggle/working/feature_space_vis/*_tsne2.csv  optional\n#   /kaggle/working/feature_space_vis/summary.csv\n# ============================================================\n\nimport os\nos.environ[\"OMP_NUM_THREADS\"] = \"4\"\nos.environ[\"OPENBLAS_NUM_THREADS\"] = \"4\"\nos.environ[\"MKL_NUM_THREADS\"] = \"4\"\nos.environ[\"NUMEXPR_NUM_THREADS\"] = \"4\"\n\nimport gc\nimport glob\nimport math\nimport random\nimport warnings\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport seaborn as sns\n\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\nfrom sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, KBinsDiscretizer\nfrom sklearn.decomposition import PCA\nfrom sklearn.manifold import TSNE\nfrom sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score\n\nwarnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")\npd.set_option(\"display.max_columns\", 200)\n\n# -----------------------------\n# Config\n# -----------------------------\nSEED = 42\nN_CPU = 4\n\n# PCAは2万程度ならかなり軽いです。\n# t-SNEをONにするなら 8k〜12k くらいがおすすめです。\nSAMPLE_N = 20000\nMAKE_TSNE = True\nTSNE_N = 10000\n\n# XGB系FEは可視化用なので、Global TEを使います。\n# 学習用ではなく「クラス分離が見える空間を確認する」目的です。\n# 厳密にCV評価へ使うならfold-safe TEにしてください。\nUSE_GLOBAL_TE_FOR_XGB_VIS = True\nTE_SMOOTH = 20.0\nTE_MAX_CARDINALITY = 5000\n\n# XGB FEのqbin統計やfrequency統計をfitする参照データ数。\n# Noneなら全量。CPU4ならまず300_000程度でも十分見えます。\nREF_SAMPLE_N_FOR_STATS = 300_000\n\nEPS = 1e-6\nTARGET = \"class\"\nID_COL = \"id\"\n\nCLASSES = [\"GALAXY\", \"QSO\", \"STAR\"]\nCLASS_TO_INT = {c: i for i, c in enumerate(CLASSES)}\nINT_TO_CLASS = {i: c for c, i in CLASS_TO_INT.items()}\n\nRAW_NUM_COLS = [\"alpha\", \"delta\", \"u\", \"g\", \"r\", \"i\", \"z\", \"redshift\"]\nRAW_CAT_COLS = [\"spectral_type\", \"galaxy_population\"]\nBANDS = [\"u\", \"g\", \"r\", \"i\", \"z\"]\n\nOUT_DIR = Path(\"/kaggle/working/feature_space_vis\")\nOUT_DIR.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\nrandom.seed(SEED)\nnp.random.seed(SEED)\n\nprint(\"OUT_DIR:\", OUT_DIR)\n\n\n# -----------------------------\n# Path helpers\n# -----------------------------\ndef find_competition_root():\n    candidates = [\n        Path(\"/kaggle/input/competitions/playground-series-s6e6\"),\n        Path(\"/kaggle/input/playground-series-s6e6\"),\n    ]\n    candidates += [Path(p).parent for p in glob.glob(\"/kaggle/input/*/train.csv\")]\n\n    for root in candidates:\n        if (root / \"train.csv\").exists() and (root / \"test.csv\").exists():\n            return root\n\n    raise FileNotFoundError(\"Could not find train.csv/test.csv.\")\n\n\ndef find_original_path():\n    candidates = [\n        Path(\"/kaggle/input/datasets/fedesoriano/stellar-classification-dataset-sdss17/star_classification.csv\"),\n    ]\n    candidates += [Path(p) for p in glob.glob(\"/kaggle/input/*/star_classification.csv\")]\n\n    for path in candidates:\n        if path.exists():\n            return path\n\n    return None\n\n\nDATA_ROOT = find_competition_root()\nORIG_PATH = find_original_path()\n\nprint(\"DATA_ROOT:\", DATA_ROOT)\nprint(\"ORIG_PATH :\", ORIG_PATH)\n\n\n# -----------------------------\n# Load data\n# -----------------------------\ntrain = pd.read_csv(DATA_ROOT / \"train.csv\")\ntest = pd.read_csv(DATA_ROOT / \"test.csv\")\n\ny = train[TARGET].map(CLASS_TO_INT).astype(np.int8).values\ny_name = train[TARGET].values\n\nprint(\"train:\", train.shape)\nprint(\"test :\", test.shape)\nprint(pd.Series(y_name).value_counts())\n\nif ORIG_PATH is not None:\n    orig = pd.read_csv(ORIG_PATH)\n    print(\"orig :\", orig.shape)\nelse:\n    orig = None\n    print(\"orig : not found. XGB original-prior features will be skipped.\")\n\n\n# -----------------------------\n# Common stratified sample\n# -----------------------------\ndef make_stratified_sample_indices(y, n, seed=42):\n    n = min(n, len(y))\n    all_idx = np.arange(len(y))\n\n    if n == len(y):\n        return all_idx\n\n    _, sample_idx = train_test_split(\n        all_idx,\n        test_size=n,\n        random_state=seed,\n        stratify=y,\n    )\n    return np.sort(sample_idx)\n\n\nsample_idx = make_stratified_sample_indices(y, SAMPLE_N, SEED)\nsample_y = y[sample_idx]\nsample_y_name = np.array([INT_TO_CLASS[int(v)] for v in sample_y])\n\nprint(\"sample_idx:\", sample_idx.shape)\nprint(pd.Series(sample_y_name).value_counts())\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# 1. Raw feature space\n# ============================================================\ndef build_raw_space(train, sample_idx):\n    cols = RAW_NUM_COLS + RAW_CAT_COLS\n    cols = [c for c in cols if c in train.columns]\n    return train.iloc[sample_idx][cols].copy()\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# 2. RealMLP-style light FE space\n#    Based on attached RealMLP FE:\n#      - g/redshift, i/redshift\n#      - u-g, u-r\n#      - string cats factorized\n#      - floor numerical categories\n#      - delta quantile bins 100/500\n#      - alpha_cat x delta_cat, u_cat x z_cat\n# ============================================================\ndef build_realmlp_light_fe_space(train, sample_idx):\n    X_all = train.drop(columns=[ID_COL, TARGET], errors=\"ignore\").copy()\n\n    cat_cols = X_all.select_dtypes(include=[\"object\"]).columns.tolist()\n    num_cols = X_all.select_dtypes(exclude=[\"object\"]).columns.tolist()\n\n    category_map = {}\n    color_pairs = [(\"u\", \"g\"), (\"u\", \"r\")]\n    important_combos = [\n        (\"alpha_cat_\", \"delta_cat_\"),\n        (\"u_cat_\", \"z_cat_\"),\n    ]\n    important_combos = sorted(important_combos)\n\n    def feature_engineering(df, fit=False):\n        df = df.copy()\n\n        # Arithmetic interaction\n        df[\"_g_/_redshift\"] = (df[\"g\"] / (df[\"redshift\"] + 1e-6)).astype(\"float32\")\n        df[\"_i_/_redshift\"] = (df[\"i\"] / (df[\"redshift\"] + 1e-6)).astype(\"float32\")\n\n        for a, b in color_pairs:\n            df[f\"_{a}-{b}\"] = (df[a] - df[b]).astype(\"float32\")\n\n        # Categorize string cats\n        for col in cat_cols:\n            if fit:\n                codes, uniques = pd.factorize(df[col].astype(str), sort=False)\n                category_map[col] = uniques\n            else:\n                uniques = category_map[col]\n                code_map = {cat: i for i, cat in enumerate(uniques)}\n                codes = df[col].astype(str).map(code_map).fillna(-1).astype(\"int32\")\n\n            df[col] = codes.astype(\"int32\")\n\n        # Categorize numericals by floor\n        for col in num_cols:\n            cat_name = f\"{col}_cat_\"\n            floored = np.floor(pd.to_numeric(df[col], errors=\"coerce\"))\n\n            if fit:\n                codes, uniques = pd.factorize(floored, sort=False)\n                category_map[col] = uniques\n            else:\n                uniques = category_map[col]\n                code_map = {cat: i for i, cat in enumerate(uniques)}\n                codes = pd.Series(floored).map(code_map).fillna(-1).astype(\"int32\").values\n\n            df[cat_name] = codes.astype(\"int32\")\n\n        # Discretize delta\n        bin_config = {\"delta\": [100, 500]}\n        for col, bins_list in bin_config.items():\n            for n_bins in bins_list:\n                bin_name = f\"{col}_{n_bins}_quantile_bin_\"\n\n                if fit:\n                    kb = KBinsDiscretizer(\n                        n_bins=n_bins,\n                        encode=\"ordinal\",\n                        strategy=\"quantile\",\n                        subsample=None,\n                    )\n                    binned = kb.fit_transform(df[[col]]).ravel().astype(\"int32\")\n                    category_map[bin_name] = kb\n                else:\n                    kb = category_map[bin_name]\n                    binned = kb.transform(df[[col]]).ravel().astype(\"int32\")\n\n                df[bin_name] = binned.astype(\"int32\")\n\n        # Interaction categories\n        for cols in important_combos:\n            combo_name = \"_\".join(cols) + \"_\"\n            combo_series = df[cols[0]].astype(str)\n\n            for col in cols[1:]:\n                combo_series = combo_series + \"_\" + df[col].astype(str)\n\n            if fit:\n                codes, uniques = pd.factorize(combo_series, sort=False)\n                category_map[combo_name] = uniques\n            else:\n                uniques = category_map[combo_name]\n                code_map = {cat: i for i, cat in enumerate(uniques)}\n                codes = combo_series.map(code_map).fillna(-1).astype(\"int32\")\n\n            df[combo_name] = codes.astype(\"int32\")\n\n        return df\n\n    X_fe_all = feature_engineering(X_all, fit=True)\n    X_fe_all = X_fe_all.reindex(sorted(X_fe_all.columns), axis=1)\n\n    return X_fe_all.iloc[sample_idx].reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# 3. XGB-style expanded FE space\n#    CPU version for visualization\n# ============================================================\ndef spectral_type_pd(g, r):\n    return pd.cut(\n        r - g,\n        [-np.inf, -1, -0.5, 0, np.inf],\n        labels=[\"M\", \"G/K\", \"A/F\", \"O/B\"],\n    ).astype(str)\n\n\ndef galaxy_population_pd(u, r):\n    return pd.cut(\n        u - r,\n        [-np.inf, 2.2, np.inf],\n        labels=[\"Blue_Cloud\", \"Red_Sequence\"],\n    ).astype(str)\n\n\ndef clean_base_competition(df, has_target):\n    keep = [c for c in [ID_COL] + RAW_NUM_COLS + RAW_CAT_COLS + ([TARGET] if has_target else []) if c in df.columns]\n    out = df[keep].copy()\n\n    for c in RAW_NUM_COLS:\n        out[c] = pd.to_numeric(out[c], errors=\"coerce\").astype(\"float32\")\n\n    for c in RAW_CAT_COLS:\n        if c in out.columns:\n            out[c] = out[c].astype(str).fillna(\"__NA__\")\n\n    return out\n\n\ndef clean_base_original(orig):\n    if orig is None:\n        return None\n\n    out = orig.copy()\n\n    missing = [c for c in RAW_NUM_COLS if c not in out.columns]\n    if missing:\n        raise ValueError(f\"Original dataset is missing required columns: {missing}\")\n\n    cols = RAW_NUM_COLS + ([TARGET] if TARGET in out.columns else [])\n    out = out[cols].copy()\n\n    for c in RAW_NUM_COLS:\n        out[c] = pd.to_numeric(out[c], errors=\"coerce\").astype(\"float32\")\n\n    out[\"spectral_type\"] = spectral_type_pd(out[\"g\"], out[\"r\"])\n    out[\"galaxy_population\"] = galaxy_population_pd(out[\"u\"], out[\"r\"])\n\n    return out\n\n\ndef add_public_features_pd(df):\n    out = df.copy()\n\n    for c in RAW_NUM_COLS:\n        out[c] = pd.to_numeric(out[c], errors=\"coerce\").astype(\"float32\")\n\n    color_pairs = [\n        (\"u\", \"g\"), (\"g\", \"r\"), (\"r\", \"i\"), (\"i\", \"z\"),\n        (\"u\", \"r\"), (\"u\", \"i\"), (\"u\", \"z\"),\n        (\"g\", \"i\"), (\"g\", \"z\"), (\"r\", \"z\"),\n    ]\n\n    for a, b in color_pairs:\n        out[f\"{a}_{b}\"] = (out[a] - out[b]).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    band_values = out[BANDS].values.astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"mag_mean\"] = np.nanmean(band_values, axis=1).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"mag_std\"] = np.nanstd(band_values, axis=1, ddof=1).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"mag_min\"] = np.nanmin(band_values, axis=1).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"mag_max\"] = np.nanmax(band_values, axis=1).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"mag_range\"] = (out[\"mag_max\"] - out[\"mag_min\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"mag_argmin\"] = np.nanargmin(np.nan_to_num(band_values, nan=np.inf), axis=1).astype(\"int16\")\n    out[\"mag_argmax\"] = np.nanargmax(np.nan_to_num(band_values, nan=-np.inf), axis=1).astype(\"int16\")\n\n    for b in BANDS:\n        out[f\"redshift_{b}\"] = (out[\"redshift\"] * out[b]).astype(\"float32\")\n        out[f\"{b}_over_redshift\"] = (out[b] / (out[\"redshift\"].abs() + EPS)).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    alpha_rad = out[\"alpha\"].values.astype(\"float32\") * np.float32(np.pi / 180.0)\n    delta_rad = out[\"delta\"].values.astype(\"float32\") * np.float32(np.pi / 180.0)\n\n    out[\"alpha_sin\"] = np.sin(alpha_rad).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"alpha_cos\"] = np.cos(alpha_rad).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"delta_sin\"] = np.sin(delta_rad).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"delta_cos\"] = np.cos(delta_rad).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"sky_x\"] = (np.cos(delta_rad) * np.cos(alpha_rad)).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"sky_y\"] = (np.cos(delta_rad) * np.sin(alpha_rad)).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"sky_z\"] = np.sin(delta_rad).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    flux_arrays = []\n    for b in BANDS:\n        clipped = np.clip(out[b].values.astype(\"float32\"), -30, 30)\n        flux = np.power(np.float32(10.0), np.float32(-0.4) * clipped).astype(\"float32\")\n        out[f\"flux_{b}\"] = flux\n        flux_arrays.append(flux)\n\n    flux_values = np.vstack(flux_arrays).T\n    out[\"flux_mean\"] = np.nanmean(flux_values, axis=1).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"flux_std\"] = np.nanstd(flux_values, axis=1, ddof=1).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"flux_min\"] = np.nanmin(flux_values, axis=1).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"flux_max\"] = np.nanmax(flux_values, axis=1).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"flux_range\"] = (out[\"flux_max\"] - out[\"flux_min\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    x = np.arange(len(BANDS), dtype=\"float32\")\n    x_centered = x - x.mean()\n    denom = np.sum(x_centered ** 2)\n    centered_bands = band_values - np.nanmean(band_values, axis=1, keepdims=True)\n    out[\"mag_slope\"] = (centered_bands @ x_centered / denom).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    out[\"mag_curvature\"] = (out[\"u\"] - 2 * out[\"r\"] + out[\"z\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"blue_curvature\"] = (out[\"u\"] - 2 * out[\"g\"] + out[\"r\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"red_curvature\"] = (out[\"r\"] - 2 * out[\"i\"] + out[\"z\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    out[\"redshift_abs\"] = out[\"redshift\"].abs().astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"redshift_log1p_abs\"] = np.log1p(out[\"redshift_abs\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n    out[\"redshift_is_neg\"] = (out[\"redshift\"] < 0).astype(\"int8\")\n\n    out[\"spectral_type_calc\"] = spectral_type_pd(out[\"g\"], out[\"r\"])\n    out[\"galaxy_population_calc\"] = galaxy_population_pd(out[\"u\"], out[\"r\"])\n\n    if \"spectral_type\" in out.columns:\n        out[\"spectral_type\"] = out[\"spectral_type\"].astype(str).fillna(\"__NA__\")\n    else:\n        out[\"spectral_type\"] = out[\"spectral_type_calc\"].astype(str)\n\n    if \"galaxy_population\" in out.columns:\n        out[\"galaxy_population\"] = out[\"galaxy_population\"].astype(str).fillna(\"__NA__\")\n    else:\n        out[\"galaxy_population\"] = out[\"galaxy_population_calc\"].astype(str)\n\n    out[\"spectral_x_pop\"] = out[\"spectral_type\"].astype(str) + \"__\" + out[\"galaxy_population\"].astype(str)\n    out[\"spectral_calc_x_pop_calc\"] = out[\"spectral_type_calc\"].astype(str) + \"__\" + out[\"galaxy_population_calc\"].astype(str)\n\n    out = out.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)\n    return out\n\n\ndef add_pairwise_geometry_features_pd(df):\n    out = df.copy()\n\n    cols = [\"u_g\", \"g_r\", \"r_i\", \"i_z\", \"u_r\", \"g_i\", \"r_z\"]\n    cols = [c for c in cols if c in out.columns]\n\n    for c in cols:\n        out[f\"{c}_x_redshift\"] = (out[c] * out[\"redshift\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n        out[f\"{c}_abs\"] = out[c].abs().astype(\"float32\")\n\n    if {\"u_g\", \"g_r\"}.issubset(out.columns):\n        ug = out[\"u_g\"].values.astype(\"float32\")\n        gr = out[\"g_r\"].values.astype(\"float32\")\n        out[\"color_plane_radius_ug_gr\"] = np.sqrt(ug ** 2 + gr ** 2).astype(\"float32\")\n        out[\"color_plane_angle_ug_gr\"] = np.arctan2(ug, gr + EPS).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    if {\"r_i\", \"i_z\"}.issubset(out.columns):\n        ri = out[\"r_i\"].values.astype(\"float32\")\n        iz = out[\"i_z\"].values.astype(\"float32\")\n        out[\"color_plane_radius_ri_iz\"] = np.sqrt(ri ** 2 + iz ** 2).astype(\"float32\")\n        out[\"color_plane_angle_ri_iz\"] = np.arctan2(ri, iz + EPS).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    return out.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)\n\n\ndef fit_qbin_edges(ref_df, cols, qs=(16, 64, 256)):\n    edges = {}\n\n    for c in cols:\n        if c not in ref_df.columns:\n            continue\n\n        s = pd.to_numeric(ref_df[c], errors=\"coerce\").dropna().values.astype(\"float32\")\n        if len(s) < 2:\n            continue\n\n        for q in qs:\n            probs = np.linspace(0, 1, q + 1)\n            bins = np.unique(np.nanquantile(s, probs))\n\n            if len(bins) <= 1:\n                continue\n\n            edges[(c, q)] = bins.astype(\"float32\")\n\n    return edges\n\n\ndef apply_qbin_edges(df, edges):\n    out = df.copy()\n    qbin_cols = []\n\n    for (c, q), bins in edges.items():\n        if c not in out.columns:\n            continue\n\n        name = f\"{c}_qbin{q}\"\n        vals = pd.to_numeric(out[c], errors=\"coerce\").values.astype(\"float32\")\n\n        codes = np.searchsorted(bins, vals, side=\"left\") - 1\n        codes[vals == bins[0]] = 0\n        codes[(vals < bins[0]) | (vals > bins[-1]) | np.isnan(vals)] = -1\n        codes = np.clip(codes, -1, len(bins) - 2).astype(\"int16\")\n\n        out[name] = codes.astype(str)\n        qbin_cols.append(name)\n\n    combo_pairs = [\n        (\"alpha_qbin64\", \"delta_qbin64\"),\n        (\"u_g_qbin64\", \"g_r_qbin64\"),\n        (\"redshift_qbin64\", \"mag_mean_qbin64\"),\n    ]\n\n    for a, b in combo_pairs:\n        if a in out.columns and b in out.columns:\n            name = f\"{a}__x__{b}\"\n            out[name] = out[a].astype(str) + \"__\" + out[b].astype(str)\n            qbin_cols.append(name)\n\n    return out, qbin_cols\n\n\ndef select_categorical_cols_for_xgb_vis(df):\n    base = [\n        \"spectral_type\",\n        \"galaxy_population\",\n        \"spectral_type_calc\",\n        \"galaxy_population_calc\",\n        \"spectral_x_pop\",\n        \"spectral_calc_x_pop_calc\",\n    ]\n\n    qbins = [\n        c for c in df.columns\n        if (\"_qbin\" in c) or (\"__x__\" in c)\n    ]\n\n    cols = base + qbins\n    cols = [c for c in dict.fromkeys(cols) if c in df.columns]\n\n    return cols\n\n\ndef filter_low_card_cols(ref_df, cols, max_card=5000):\n    keep = []\n    for c in cols:\n        card = ref_df[c].astype(str).nunique(dropna=False)\n        if card <= max_card:\n            keep.append(c)\n    return keep\n\n\ndef add_frequency_features_sample(X_sample, ref_df, cat_cols):\n    out = X_sample.copy()\n\n    for c in cat_cols:\n        if c not in out.columns or c not in ref_df.columns:\n            continue\n\n        vc = ref_df[c].astype(str).value_counts(dropna=False)\n        out[f\"{c}_freq\"] = out[c].astype(str).map(vc).fillna(0).astype(\"float32\")\n        out[f\"{c}_freq_log1p\"] = np.log1p(out[f\"{c}_freq\"]).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    return out\n\n\ndef add_original_prior_features_sample(X_sample, orig_ref, y_orig, cat_cols, smooth=20.0):\n    out = X_sample.copy()\n\n    if orig_ref is None or y_orig is None:\n        return out\n\n    y_orig = np.asarray(y_orig).astype(int)\n    priors = np.bincount(y_orig, minlength=len(CLASSES)).astype(\"float64\")\n    priors = priors / max(priors.sum(), 1)\n\n    for c in cat_cols:\n        if c not in out.columns or c not in orig_ref.columns:\n            continue\n\n        tmp = pd.DataFrame({\n            \"key\": orig_ref[c].astype(str).values,\n            \"y\": y_orig,\n        })\n\n        counts = tmp.groupby(\"key\")[\"y\"].size()\n        out[f\"orig_{c}_count\"] = out[c].astype(str).map(counts).fillna(0).astype(\"float32\")\n\n        for cls_idx, cls_name in INT_TO_CLASS.items():\n            hit = (tmp[\"y\"].values == cls_idx).astype(\"float32\")\n            tmp_hit = pd.DataFrame({\"key\": tmp[\"key\"].values, \"hit\": hit})\n\n            sums = tmp_hit.groupby(\"key\")[\"hit\"].sum()\n            cnts = counts.reindex(sums.index).astype(\"float64\")\n\n            rates = (sums + priors[cls_idx] * smooth) / (cnts + smooth)\n            out[f\"orig_{c}_prior_{cls_name}\"] = (\n                out[c].astype(str).map(rates).fillna(priors[cls_idx]).astype(\"float32\")\n            )\n\n    return out\n\n\ndef add_global_te_features_sample(X_sample, train_ref, y_train, cat_cols, smooth=20.0):\n    out = X_sample.copy()\n\n    y_train = np.asarray(y_train).astype(int)\n    priors = np.bincount(y_train, minlength=len(CLASSES)).astype(\"float64\")\n    priors = priors / max(priors.sum(), 1)\n\n    for c in cat_cols:\n        if c not in out.columns or c not in train_ref.columns:\n            continue\n\n        tmp = pd.DataFrame({\n            \"key\": train_ref[c].astype(str).values,\n            \"y\": y_train,\n        })\n\n        counts = tmp.groupby(\"key\")[\"y\"].size().astype(\"float64\")\n\n        for cls_idx, cls_name in INT_TO_CLASS.items():\n            hit = (tmp[\"y\"].values == cls_idx).astype(\"float32\")\n            tmp_hit = pd.DataFrame({\"key\": tmp[\"key\"].values, \"hit\": hit})\n\n            sums = tmp_hit.groupby(\"key\")[\"hit\"].sum()\n            cnts = counts.reindex(sums.index).astype(\"float64\")\n\n            rates = (sums + priors[cls_idx] * smooth) / (cnts + smooth)\n            out[f\"TE_{c}_{cls_name}\"] = (\n                out[c].astype(str).map(rates).fillna(priors[cls_idx]).astype(\"float32\")\n            )\n\n    return out\n\n\ndef build_xgb_expanded_fe_space(train, test, orig, sample_idx):\n    print(\"\\nBuilding XGB-style expanded FE space...\")\n\n    train_base = clean_base_competition(train, has_target=True)\n    test_base = clean_base_competition(test, has_target=False)\n    orig_base = clean_base_original(orig) if orig is not None else None\n\n    y_train_int = train_base[TARGET].map(CLASS_TO_INT).astype(np.int8).values\n\n    if orig_base is not None and TARGET in orig_base.columns:\n        y_orig_int = orig_base[TARGET].map(CLASS_TO_INT).astype(np.int8).values\n    else:\n        y_orig_int = None\n\n    # sample rows to visualize\n    X_sample_base = train_base.iloc[sample_idx].drop(columns=[ID_COL, TARGET], errors=\"ignore\").reset_index(drop=True)\n\n    # reference for train/test quantiles and frequency\n    tt_base = pd.concat(\n        [\n            train_base.drop(columns=[ID_COL, TARGET], errors=\"ignore\"),\n            test_base.drop(columns=[ID_COL], errors=\"ignore\"),\n        ],\n        axis=0,\n        ignore_index=True,\n    )\n\n    if REF_SAMPLE_N_FOR_STATS is not None and len(tt_base) > REF_SAMPLE_N_FOR_STATS:\n        tt_ref_base = tt_base.sample(\n            n=REF_SAMPLE_N_FOR_STATS,\n            random_state=SEED,\n            replace=False,\n        ).reset_index(drop=True)\n    else:\n        tt_ref_base = tt_base.reset_index(drop=True)\n\n    # Full train ref is needed for TE mapping.\n    train_ref_base = train_base.drop(columns=[ID_COL, TARGET], errors=\"ignore\").reset_index(drop=True)\n\n    # Original ref for prior features.\n    if orig_base is not None:\n        orig_ref_base = orig_base.drop(columns=[TARGET], errors=\"ignore\").reset_index(drop=True)\n    else:\n        orig_ref_base = None\n\n    # Public + geometry\n    X_sample = add_pairwise_geometry_features_pd(add_public_features_pd(X_sample_base))\n    tt_ref = add_pairwise_geometry_features_pd(add_public_features_pd(tt_ref_base))\n    train_ref = add_pairwise_geometry_features_pd(add_public_features_pd(train_ref_base))\n\n    if orig_ref_base is not None:\n        orig_ref = add_pairwise_geometry_features_pd(add_public_features_pd(orig_ref_base))\n    else:\n        orig_ref = None\n\n    qbin_base_cols = RAW_NUM_COLS + [\n        c for c in [\"u_g\", \"g_r\", \"r_i\", \"i_z\", \"u_r\", \"mag_mean\", \"mag_range\"]\n        if c in tt_ref.columns\n    ]\n\n    edges = fit_qbin_edges(tt_ref, qbin_base_cols, qs=(16, 64, 256))\n\n    X_sample, _ = apply_qbin_edges(X_sample, edges)\n    tt_ref, _ = apply_qbin_edges(tt_ref, edges)\n    train_ref, _ = apply_qbin_edges(train_ref, edges)\n\n    if orig_ref is not None:\n        orig_ref, _ = apply_qbin_edges(orig_ref, edges)\n\n    cat_cols = select_categorical_cols_for_xgb_vis(X_sample)\n    cat_cols = filter_low_card_cols(tt_ref, cat_cols, max_card=TE_MAX_CARDINALITY * 4)\n\n    print(\"XGB-vis cat_cols:\", len(cat_cols))\n\n    # frequency fit source: train/test ref + original ref\n    if orig_ref is not None:\n        freq_ref = pd.concat(\n            [tt_ref[cat_cols], orig_ref[[c for c in cat_cols if c in orig_ref.columns]]],\n            axis=0,\n            ignore_index=True,\n        )\n    else:\n        freq_ref = tt_ref[cat_cols].copy()\n\n    X_sample = add_frequency_features_sample(X_sample, freq_ref, cat_cols)\n\n    # original prior features\n    if orig_ref is not None and y_orig_int is not None:\n        X_sample = add_original_prior_features_sample(\n            X_sample,\n            orig_ref,\n            y_orig_int,\n            cat_cols,\n            smooth=TE_SMOOTH,\n        )\n\n    # Global TE for visualization\n    if USE_GLOBAL_TE_FOR_XGB_VIS:\n        te_cols = filter_low_card_cols(train_ref, cat_cols, max_card=TE_MAX_CARDINALITY)\n        print(\"Global TE cols for visualization:\", len(te_cols))\n        X_sample = add_global_te_features_sample(\n            X_sample,\n            train_ref,\n            y_train_int,\n            te_cols,\n            smooth=TE_SMOOTH,\n        )\n\n    # Remove id/target if any\n    X_sample = X_sample.drop(columns=[ID_COL, TARGET], errors=\"ignore\")\n    X_sample = X_sample.replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)\n\n    print(\"XGB-style FE sample shape:\", X_sample.shape)\n\n    del train_base, test_base, orig_base, tt_base, tt_ref_base\n    del X_sample_base, tt_ref, train_ref, freq_ref\n    gc.collect()\n\n    return X_sample.reset_index(drop=True)\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# 4. OOF stacking logit space\n# ============================================================\nEPS_STACK = 1e-15\nLOGIT_CLIP = 30.0\n\nSTACKING_FILES = [\n    (\"xgb-0\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/xgb-v0-for-s6e6/oof_xgb_cv.csv\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/xgb-v0-for-s6e6/test_xgb_preds.csv\"),\n    (\"xgb-1\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/xgb-v1-for-s6e6/oof_preds.npy\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/xgb-v1-for-s6e6/test_preds.npy\"),\n    (\"realmlp-0\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/yekenot/ps-s6-e6-realmlp-pytorch/oof_preds.csv\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/yekenot/ps-s6-e6-realmlp-pytorch/test_preds.csv\"),\n    (\"realmlp-1\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/realmlp-v1-for-s6e6/oof_preds.npy\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/realmlp-v1-for-s6e6/test_preds.npy\"),\n    (\"tabm-0\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/donmarch14/s6e6-tabm/oof_preds.csv\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/donmarch14/s6e6-tabm/test_preds.csv\"),\n    (\"cat-0\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/cat-v0-for-s6e6/catboost_oof_predictions.csv\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/cat-v0-for-s6e6/catboost_test_predictions.csv\"),\n    (\"realmlp-2\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/nawfeelrahman1124444/single-realmlp-0-96973-ridge-pl/oof_preds_realmlp.csv\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/nawfeelrahman1124444/single-realmlp-0-96973-ridge-pl/test_preds_realmlp.csv\"),\n    (\"tabicl-2\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/tabicl-v2-for-s6e6/train_oof/tabicl-2_oof.npy\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/tabicl-v2-for-s6e6/test_preds/tabicl-2_test_preds.npy\"),\n    (\"lgbm-3\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/lgbm-v3-for-s6e6/train_oof/lgbm-3_oof.npy\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/lgbm-v3-for-s6e6/test_preds/lgbm-3_test_preds.npy\"),\n    (\"logreg-1\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/logreg-v1-for-s6e6/train_oof/logreg-1_oof.npy\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/logreg-v1-for-s6e6/test_preds/logreg-1_test_preds.npy\"),\n    (\"nn-1\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/nn-v1-for-s6e6/train_oof/nn-1_oof.npy\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/nn-v1-for-s6e6/test_preds/nn-1_test_preds.npy\"),\n    (\"xgb-3\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/xgb-v3-for-s6e6/stellar_class_xgb_oof_preds_raw.npy\", \"/kaggle/input/notebooks/cdeotte/xgb-v3-for-s6e6/stellar_class_xgb_test_preds_raw.npy\"),\n]\n\n\ndef prob_to_logit(p):\n    p = np.clip(p, EPS_STACK, 1.0 - EPS_STACK).astype(np.float64)\n    return np.clip(np.log(p / (1.0 - p)), -LOGIT_CLIP, LOGIT_CLIP).astype(np.float32)\n\n\ndef load_preds(path, expected_rows=None):\n    if path.lower().endswith(\".csv\"):\n        df = pd.read_csv(path)\n\n        # broken flattened CSV with one column\n        if df.shape[1] == 1:\n            vals = df.iloc[:, 0].values\n            if expected_rows is not None:\n                assert len(vals) == expected_rows * 3, (\n                    f\"{path}: one-column CSV length={len(vals)}, \"\n                    f\"expected={expected_rows * 3}\"\n                )\n            assert len(vals) % 3 == 0\n            return vals.reshape(-1, 3)\n\n        # normal CSV: use last 3 columns\n        return df.iloc[:, -3:].values[:expected_rows]\n\n    arr = np.load(path)\n\n    if arr.ndim == 3:\n        arr = arr.mean(axis=0)\n\n    return arr[:expected_rows] if expected_rows is not None else arr\n\n\ndef build_oof_stack_logit_space(sample_idx, expected_rows):\n    loaded = []\n    names = []\n\n    print(\"\\nLoading OOF stack files:\")\n    for name, oof_path, _ in STACKING_FILES:\n        try:\n            o = load_preds(oof_path, expected_rows=expected_rows)\n            o = prob_to_logit(o)\n\n            assert o.shape == (expected_rows, 3), f\"{name}: OOF shape={o.shape}\"\n\n            loaded.append(o)\n            names.append(name)\n\n            print(f\"  OK   {name:15s} {o.shape}\")\n\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"  SKIP {name:15s}: {e}\")\n\n    if len(loaded) == 0:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"No OOF files loaded. Please update STACKING_FILES paths.\")\n\n    X_stack = np.concatenate(loaded, axis=1).astype(\"float32\")\n    cols = []\n    for name in names:\n        for cls_name in CLASSES:\n            cols.append(f\"{name}_{cls_name}_logit\")\n\n    X_stack_sample = pd.DataFrame(X_stack[sample_idx], columns=cols)\n\n    print(\"OOF stack logit sample shape:\", X_stack_sample.shape)\n    return X_stack_sample\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# Numeric conversion + dimensionality reduction\n# ============================================================\ndef dataframe_to_numeric_matrix(df):\n    arrays = []\n    names = []\n\n    for c in df.columns:\n        s = df[c]\n\n        if pd.api.types.is_numeric_dtype(s):\n            arr = pd.to_numeric(s, errors=\"coerce\").values.astype(\"float32\")\n        else:\n            arr = pd.factorize(s.astype(str).fillna(\"__NA__\"), sort=True)[0].astype(\"float32\")\n\n        arrays.append(arr)\n        names.append(c)\n\n    X = np.column_stack(arrays).astype(\"float32\")\n    X[~np.isfinite(X)] = np.nan\n\n    med = np.nanmedian(X, axis=0)\n    med[~np.isfinite(med)] = 0.0\n    X = np.where(np.isnan(X), med[None, :], X)\n\n    # drop constant columns\n    std = np.nanstd(X, axis=0)\n    keep = std > 1e-12\n    X = X[:, keep]\n    names = [n for n, k in zip(names, keep) if k]\n\n    return X.astype(\"float32\"), names\n\n\ndef stratified_subsample_local(y_local, n, seed):\n    n = min(n, len(y_local))\n    idx = np.arange(len(y_local))\n\n    if n == len(y_local):\n        return idx\n\n    _, sub = train_test_split(\n        idx,\n        test_size=n,\n        random_state=seed,\n        stratify=y_local,\n    )\n    return np.sort(sub)\n\n\ndef safe_silhouette_2d(Z, y_local, max_n=5000):\n    if len(Z) < 100:\n        return np.nan\n\n    idx = stratified_subsample_local(y_local, min(max_n, len(y_local)), SEED)\n    try:\n        return silhouette_score(Z[idx], y_local[idx])\n    except Exception:\n        return np.nan\n\n\ndef make_pca_embedding(space_name, X_df, y_local, y_name_local):\n    X, feature_names = dataframe_to_numeric_matrix(X_df)\n    print(f\"\\n[{space_name}] numeric matrix:\", X.shape)\n\n    scaler = StandardScaler()\n    Xs = scaler.fit_transform(X).astype(\"float32\")\n\n    n_comp = min(50, Xs.shape[1], Xs.shape[0] - 1)\n    pca = PCA(n_components=n_comp, random_state=SEED, svd_solver=\"randomized\")\n    Z = pca.fit_transform(Xs)\n\n    emb = pd.DataFrame({\n        \"x\": Z[:, 0],\n        \"y\": Z[:, 1],\n        \"class\": y_name_local,\n        \"class_id\": y_local,\n    })\n\n    emb[\"space\"] = space_name\n    emb[\"method\"] = \"PCA\"\n\n    explained_2d = float(pca.explained_variance_ratio_[:2].sum())\n    sil2d = safe_silhouette_2d(emb[[\"x\", \"y\"]].values, y_local)\n\n    emb.to_csv(OUT_DIR / f\"{space_name}_pca2.csv\", index=False)\n\n    info = {\n        \"space\": space_name,\n        \"method\": \"PCA\",\n        \"n_rows\": len(X_df),\n        \"n_features_after_numeric\": X.shape[1],\n        \"pca_explained_var_2d\": explained_2d,\n        \"silhouette_2d\": sil2d,\n    }\n\n    return emb, info, Xs\n\n\ndef make_tsne_embedding(space_name, Xs, y_local, y_name_local):\n    idx = stratified_subsample_local(y_local, TSNE_N, SEED)\n    X_sub = Xs[idx]\n    y_sub = y_local[idx]\n    y_name_sub = y_name_local[idx]\n\n    n_comp = min(30, X_sub.shape[1], X_sub.shape[0] - 1)\n    X_pca = PCA(\n        n_components=n_comp,\n        random_state=SEED,\n        svd_solver=\"randomized\",\n    ).fit_transform(X_sub)\n\n    print(f\"[{space_name}] t-SNE input:\", X_pca.shape)\n\n    tsne = TSNE(\n        n_components=2,\n        perplexity=40,\n        learning_rate=\"auto\",\n        init=\"pca\",\n        random_state=SEED,\n        n_jobs=N_CPU,\n        method=\"barnes_hut\",\n        verbose=1,\n    )\n\n    Z = tsne.fit_transform(X_pca)\n\n    emb = pd.DataFrame({\n        \"x\": Z[:, 0],\n        \"y\": Z[:, 1],\n        \"class\": y_name_sub,\n        \"class_id\": y_sub,\n    })\n\n    emb[\"space\"] = space_name\n    emb[\"method\"] = \"t-SNE\"\n\n    sil2d = safe_silhouette_2d(emb[[\"x\", \"y\"]].values, y_sub)\n\n    emb.to_csv(OUT_DIR / f\"{space_name}_tsne2.csv\", index=False)\n\n    info = {\n        \"space\": space_name,\n        \"method\": \"t-SNE\",\n        \"n_rows\": len(emb),\n        \"n_features_after_numeric\": Xs.shape[1],\n        \"pca_explained_var_2d\": np.nan,\n        \"silhouette_2d\": sil2d,\n    }\n\n    return emb, info\n\n\ndef plot_embedding(emb, title, path):\n    plt.figure(figsize=(7, 6))\n    sns.scatterplot(\n        data=emb,\n        x=\"x\",\n        y=\"y\",\n        hue=\"class\",\n        hue_order=CLASSES,\n        s=8,\n        alpha=0.55,\n        linewidth=0,\n    )\n    plt.title(title)\n    plt.xlabel(\"dim 1\")\n    plt.ylabel(\"dim 2\")\n    plt.legend(markerscale=2, frameon=True)\n    plt.tight_layout()\n    plt.savefig(path, dpi=180)\n    plt.show()\n\n\ndef plot_grid(embeddings, method):\n    names = list(embeddings.keys())\n    n = len(names)\n\n    fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, n, figsize=(6 * n, 5), squeeze=False)\n    axes = axes.ravel()\n\n    for ax, name in zip(axes, names):\n        emb = embeddings[name]\n\n        for cls in CLASSES:\n            m = emb[\"class\"].values == cls\n            ax.scatter(\n                emb.loc[m, \"x\"],\n                emb.loc[m, \"y\"],\n                s=5,\n                alpha=0.50,\n                label=cls,\n            )\n\n        ax.set_title(name)\n        ax.set_xlabel(\"dim 1\")\n        ax.set_ylabel(\"dim 2\")\n\n    handles, labels = axes[0].get_legend_handles_labels()\n    fig.legend(handles, labels, loc=\"upper center\", ncol=len(CLASSES))\n    fig.suptitle(f\"{method} feature space comparison\", y=1.05, fontsize=16)\n    fig.tight_layout()\n    path = OUT_DIR / f\"grid_{method.lower()}_comparison.png\"\n    plt.savefig(path, dpi=180, bbox_inches=\"tight\")\n    plt.show()\n\n    print(\"Saved:\", path)\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# Build all spaces\n# ============================================================\nspaces = {}\n\nprint(\"\\nBuilding raw space...\")\nspaces[\"raw\"] = build_raw_space(train, sample_idx).reset_index(drop=True)\nprint(\"raw:\", spaces[\"raw\"].shape)\n\nprint(\"\\nBuilding RealMLP-light FE space...\")\nspaces[\"realmlp_light_fe\"] = build_realmlp_light_fe_space(train, sample_idx)\nprint(\"realmlp_light_fe:\", spaces[\"realmlp_light_fe\"].shape)\n\nspaces[\"xgb_expanded_fe\"] = build_xgb_expanded_fe_space(train, test, orig, sample_idx)\nprint(\"xgb_expanded_fe:\", spaces[\"xgb_expanded_fe\"].shape)\n\nspaces[\"oof_stack_logit\"] = build_oof_stack_logit_space(sample_idx, expected_rows=len(train))\nprint(\"oof_stack_logit:\", spaces[\"oof_stack_logit\"].shape)\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# PCA + optional t-SNE visualization\n# ============================================================\npca_embeddings = {}\ntsne_embeddings = {}\nsummary_rows = {}\n\nfor space_name, X_df in spaces.items():\n    emb_pca, info_pca, Xs = make_pca_embedding(\n        space_name,\n        X_df,\n        sample_y,\n        sample_y_name,\n    )\n\n    pca_embeddings[space_name] = emb_pca\n    summary_rows[(space_name, \"PCA\")] = info_pca\n\n    plot_embedding(\n        emb_pca,\n        title=(\n            f\"{space_name} | PCA 2D \"\n            f\"| explained={info_pca['pca_explained_var_2d']:.3f} \"\n            f\"| sil={info_pca['silhouette_2d']:.3f}\"\n        ),\n        path=OUT_DIR / f\"{space_name}_pca2.png\",\n    )\n\n    if MAKE_TSNE:\n        emb_tsne, info_tsne = make_tsne_embedding(\n            space_name,\n            Xs,\n            sample_y,\n            sample_y_name,\n        )\n\n        tsne_embeddings[space_name] = emb_tsne\n        summary_rows[(space_name, \"t-SNE\")] = info_tsne\n\n        plot_embedding(\n            emb_tsne,\n            title=(\n                f\"{space_name} | t-SNE 2D \"\n                f\"| sil={info_tsne['silhouette_2d']:.3f}\"\n            ),\n            path=OUT_DIR / f\"{space_name}_tsne2.png\",\n        )\n\n    del Xs\n    gc.collect()\n\n\nplot_grid(pca_embeddings, method=\"PCA\")\n\nif MAKE_TSNE:\n    plot_grid(tsne_embeddings, method=\"t-SNE\")\n\n\nsummary = pd.DataFrame(list(summary_rows.values()))\nsummary.to_csv(OUT_DIR / \"summary.csv\", index=False)\n\nprint(\"\\nSummary:\")\ndisplay(summary)\n\nprint(\"\\nSaved files:\")\nfor p in sorted(OUT_DIR.glob(\"*\")):\n    print(p)","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-06-05T01:13:03.578209Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-06-05T01:13:03.578645Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-06-05T01:18:21.744324Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-06-05T01:13:03.578602Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-06-05T01:18:21.743584Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"code","source":"","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null}]}